{
  "text": "Based on CD28 expression, another Treg population has previously been described in humans. Cyclic stimulations of PBMCs with allogenic APC induced CD8 + T cells deprived of CD28 expression, which inhibited cellular proliferation in these in vitro cultures [CITATION_1] . Since then, several groups have tried to develop, with more or less success, their own strategies to induce CD8 + CD28 − Treg in vitro by stimulating PBMCs with cocktails of cytokines in the presence or absence of antigens [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , with phorbol12-myristate 13-acetate/ionomycin or phytohemagglutinin [CITATION_4] or with a recombinant immunoglobulin-like transcript 3 (ILT3)-Fc fusion protein [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . CD8 +",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "36030949",
    "[CITATION_2]": "37373712",
    "[CITATION_3]": "16853459",
    "[CITATION_4]": "21377885",
